# Uro, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Uro () is a rural locality (a selo) in Barguzinsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 1,160 as of 2010. There are 13 streets.
Geography
Uro is located 25&nbsp;km southeast of Barguzin (the district's administrative centre) by road. Maloye Uro is the nearest rural locality.
